    ],
    "banned_moves": [
      "add an explicit bias measure such as a feeling thermometer or social distance scale",
      "extend the intervention to multiple sessions or a longitudinal program",
      "include a neuroimaging or physiological arousal component"
    ],
    "final_proposal": "### Research Proposal: Structured Cooperative Task Intergroup Contact\n\n#### Core Hypothesis\nParticipants who engage in a 90-minute structured cooperative problem-solving task with an outgroup member will exhibit a statistically significant reduction in implicit racial bias (measured via the IAT) at the 2-week follow-up compared to participants in a solo-task control group. The predicted minimum effect size is Cohen\u2019s *d* = 0.20.\n\n#### Minimal Viable Design\n*   **Sample:** $N = 400$ (200 Treatment, 200 Control). Power analysis accounts for IAT test-retest reliability ($r \\approx 0.5$) to ensure sufficient sensitivity.\n*   **Arms:**\n    *   **Treatment:** Participants complete a 90-minute \"Jigsaw\" style collaborative task (e.g., reaching a consensus on a complex resource-allocation problem) with an outgroup partner.\n    *   **Control:** Participants complete the same 90-minute task individually to isolate the effect of \"contact\" vs. \"task engagement.\"\n*   **Procedure:**\n    1.  **Baseline:** Remote IAT via Project Implicit.\n    2.  **Session:** 90-minute intervention/control task via secure video conferencing.\n    3.  **Manipulation Check:** Post-intervention survey item: \"To what extent did you perceive this task as a collaborative interaction with someone from a different racial/ethnic group?\" (Likert scale 1\u20137).\n    4.  **Follow-up:** Exactly 14 days later, participants complete a second IAT via Project Implicit.\n\n#### Primary Outcome\nThe change score in IAT $D$-scores (Follow-up minus Baseline). A lower $D$-score at follow-up indicates reduced implicit bias.\n\n#### Main Confound and Mitigation\n*   **Confound:** Social desirability bias resulting from the nature of the contact session. \n*   **Mitigation:** The control group performs the identical task solo; because both groups perform the task for 90 minutes, the cognitive load and \"effort\" are held constant, neutralizing the effect of general task engagement on IAT performance.\n\n#### Two Plausible Alternatives Not Chosen\n1.  **Virtual Reality (VR) Shared-Experience:** Rejected due to high technical complexity and equipment variability, which risks introducing noise that threatens the fidelity of the \"intergroup contact\" variable.\n2.  **Structured Perspective-Taking:** Rejected because it relies heavily on participant introspection and internal effort, which is harder to standardize across participants than the performance-based metrics of a cooperative task.\n\n***"
  },
